\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. R. suffruticosus} Gay ex Meissner in DC., {\i Prodr. }{\b 14:} 72 (1856). Stems densely branched, dark and woody at the base; flowering branches herbaceous, erect. Leaves narrowly linear, hastate, with long, narrow basal lobes diverging at right-angles. Outer perianth-segments free, appressed to the margins of the valves. Inflorescence small, narrow, usually lax; branches simple. Valves c. 3 × 3 mm, dark brown. •{\i  Mountains of N. & C. Spain; one station in E.C. Portugal}. Hs Lu.
\par

