\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b scutatus} (incl. subsp.{\i  gallaecicus} Lago): Inflorescence more or less leafy, with few branches; flowering branches not becoming indurate in fruit, forming a loose mass. 2n = 20.{\i  Usually calcicole. Throughout most of the range of the species, except Portugal}.
