\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. R. nivalis} Hegetschw.,{\i  Fl. Schweiz }345 (1839). Stems 7-20 cm, several from a thick stock, leafless or with 1 or 2 cauline leaves. Leaves small; outermost (or sometimes all) basal leaves rounded at the apex, slightly cordate at the base, without basal lobes; cauline leaves (if present) and sometimes inner basal leaves more or less hastate. Inflorescence lax, usually simple, rarely with 1 or 2 short branches. Valves c. 3 mm. Nut pale brown. 2n = 14(female), 15(male).{\i  Stony places in the mountains above} 1500 {\i m; calcicole. Alps; S.W. Jugoslavia.} Al Au Ge He It Ju.
