\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. R. alpestris} Jacq., {\i Enum. Stirp. Vindob.} 62 (1762) ({\i R. arifolius} All.,{\i  R. carpaticus} Rech. fil.,{\i  R. montanus} Desf.; incl. {\i R. amplexicaulis} Lapeyr.). Stems (10-)50-120 cm, with numerous cauline leaves. Basal leaves ovate, about twice as long as wide, cordate at the base with short, truncate or rounded basal lobes; upper leaves sagittate. Ochreae more or less entire. Panicle lax, with flexuous branches, the lower sometimes branched. Valves 3·3-4·5 mm long and wide. Nut 2·5-3 mm, usually yellowish-grey (rarely brown), dull. 2n = 14(female), 15(male).{\i  Meadows; mainly on mountains in the south. N. Europe, southwards to S. Norway; C. & S. Europe, from C. Germany to N. Greece and N. Spain.} Au Bu Co Cz Fe Ga Ge Gr He Hs It Ju ?Lu No Po Rm Rs(N, W) ?Sa Su.
